  "texts": [
    "Phase two (mid-march to late march): remediationIn phase one, there are no concrete guidelines released by any of the universities.",
    "Although the CUHK student who got caught may not be the only case of students using ChatGPT to complete course assignments, it was the first case that was published in the local newspaper.",
    "Two days after the incident, CUHK quickly released the \"Use of Artificial Intelligence Tools in Teaching, Learning, and Assessments: A Guide for Students\", 3 becoming the first local university to publish a guideline on the use of AI tools for students.",
    "CUHK has stated a general principle of using AI tools and explicitly stated that using AI without permission will be deemed as serious academic dishonesty that has penalties, which may include a review of assessments, permanent demerits, failing the course, suspension, a lower degree classification, expulsion, or even revoking academic certification, following the university's procedures for handling cases of academic dishonesty.",
    "The guideline issued by CUHK aims to bring out a deterrent effect to prevent students from abusing AI tools in their academic studies."
